name: Jumping Jacks
description: A basic calisthenics exercise performed by jumping to a position with legs spread wide and hands touching overhead, then returning to a position with the feet together and the arms at the sides.

name: Burpees
description: A full-body exercise that involves a squat, a push-up, and a jump. It's performed in a continuous motion.

name: High Knees
description: A cardiovascular exercise where a person raises their knees high alternatively while standing in place.

name: Mountain Climbers
description: A dynamic exercise that targets multiple muscle groups, including the core, shoulders, and legs. It mimics the motion of climbing a mountain.

name: Squat Jumps
description: A plyometric exercise that combines a squat with an explosive jump, targeting the legs and glutes.

name: Plank Jacks
description: A variation of the plank exercise where the legs are alternately moved out and in, similar to the motion of doing jumping jacks.

name: Jump Lunges
description: A plyometric exercise that combines a lunge with a jump, targeting the legs and improving explosive strength.

name: Push-ups
description: A classic bodyweight exercise that targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps.

name: Bicycle Crunches
description: A core-strengthening exercise that involves bringing the knees in while simultaneously twisting the torso.

name: Box Jumps
description: A plyometric exercise where a person jumps onto a box or platform, targeting the legs and improving explosive power.

name: Russian Twists
description: A core exercise that involves twisting the torso from side to side while holding a weight or keeping the hands clasped together.

name: Sprinting in Place
description: A high-intensity cardiovascular exercise performed by running in place at maximum speed.

name: Jump Rope
description: A cardiovascular exercise involving jumping over a rope as it passes under your feet.

name: Wall Sits
description: A static exercise where a person sits against a wall with knees bent at a 90-degree angle, holding the position for a period of time.

name: Skater Jumps
description: A lateral plyometric exercise that mimics the motion of a speed skater, targeting the legs and improving balance.

name: Alternating Side Lunges
description: A lower-body exercise that involves stepping to the side and lowering the body into a lunge position, alternating sides.

name: Tricep Dips
description: An exercise that targets the triceps by using a bench or chair to support the body while dipping down and pushing back up.

name: Plyometric Push-ups
description: A variation of the traditional push-up that includes an explosive push-off from the ground, increasing power and strength.

name: Sit-ups
description: A classic abdominal exercise that involves lying on the back, bending the knees, and sitting up to touch the elbows to the knees.

name: Speed Skaters
description: A dynamic exercise that mimics the motion of a speed skater, involving lateral jumps from side to side.

name: Side Plank with Hip Dip
description: A variation of the side plank exercise where the hips are dipped up and down to engage the obliques.

name: Jump Squats
description: A plyometric exercise combining a squat with an explosive jump, targeting the legs and improving lower body power.

name: Lateral Bounds
description: A plyometric exercise that involves jumping laterally from side to side, improving agility and leg strength.

name: Superman Holds
description: A core-strengthening exercise that involves lying face down and lifting the arms and legs off the ground, resembling the flying position of Superman.

name: Inchworms
description: A dynamic stretching exercise that involves walking the hands out into a plank position, then walking the feet towards the hands to return to a standing position.

name: Alternating Reverse Lunges
description: A lower-body exercise that involves stepping back into a lunge position, alternating legs.

name: Fast Feet Drill
description: A cardio drill involving rapid movement of the feet while staying in place, typically performed for a short duration.

name: Plank with Shoulder Taps
description: A core-stabilizing exercise performed in a plank position with alternating shoulder taps.

name: Tuck Jumps
description: A plyometric exercise that involves jumping up while bringing the knees towards the chest.

name: Crab Walks
description: A functional exercise that targets the entire body, involving walking on hands and feet with the hips lifted off the ground.

name: Single-Leg Deadlifts
description: A unilateral lower-body exercise that targets the hamstrings, glutes, and lower back.

name: Power Push-ups
description: An explosive variation of the push-up exercise, performed with enough force to lift the hands off the ground.

name: V-ups
description: A challenging core exercise where the body forms a V shape by lifting the legs and upper body simultaneously.

name: Spider Lunges
description: A dynamic lower-body exercise that combines a lunge with a rotation, mimicking the movement of a spider crawling.

name: Star Jumps
description: A plyometric exercise that involves jumping up with arms and legs spread wide, resembling the shape of a star.

name: Alternating Jump Lunges
description: A dynamic lower-body exercise that combines a lunge with a jump, alternating legs with each repetition.

name: Bear Crawls
description: A functional exercise that mimics the movement of a bear, involving crawling forward and backward on hands and feet.

name: Pike Push-ups
description: A bodyweight exercise that targets the shoulders and triceps, performed with the hips raised in a pike position.

name: Flutter Kicks
description: A core exercise performed by lying on the back and alternately fluttering the legs up and down without touching the ground.

name: Donkey Kicks
description: A lower-body exercise that targets the glutes and hamstrings, involving kicking the legs back while in a quadruped position.

name: Side-to-Side Jump Lunges
description: A dynamic lower-body exercise that combines a lateral jump with a lunge, alternating sides.

name: Alternating Single Leg V-ups
description: A core exercise that targets the abdominals and hip flexors, involving lifting one leg and reaching for it with the opposite hand while lying on the back.

name: Explosive Step-ups
description: A plyometric exercise that involves stepping up onto a platform with enough force to propel the body off the ground.

name: Commando Plank
description: A variation of the plank exercise that involves transitioning between forearm and extended arm positions.

name: Side Plank with Leg Lift
description: A variation of the side plank exercise that involves lifting the top leg to engage the abductors and glutes.

name: Squat Thrusts
description: A full-body exercise that combines a squat with a plank, performed in a fast-paced manner.

name: Fast Punches (shadow boxing)
description: A cardiovascular exercise involving rapid punches thrown in the air, simulating a boxing motion.

name: Reverse Crunches
description: A core exercise that targets the lower abs, involving lifting the hips off the ground while lying on the back.

name: Plank to Push-up
description: A dynamic exercise that involves moving from a plank position to a push-up position and back again.
